for personal taxes owed because by moving the higher number for example 20mm , you incur
another 40% hit on the 7 million , that did get offset by avoiding paying 40% on the 13mm
you would have paid as a dividend. Also if you are using the 20mm to pay off related
company debt, it creates another tax issue as you took the money out of that entity to pay
your taxes.

Not critical to the deal but my job to make money not give it away.

Bob
